# Template Responsiveness — Required for ALL Templates

Every template (existing and new) must render correctly on all these viewports:

| Device class | Width range |
|---|---|
| Mobile (iPhone SE, Android) | 320px – 480px |
| Large phone (iPhone Pro Max, Android XL) | 481px – 767px |
| Tablet / iPad | 768px – 1024px |
| Laptop / MacBook | 1025px – 1440px |
| Desktop | 1441px+ |

---

## Rules

### 1. Never use viewport units (`vw`, `vh`) in templates
Templates render at a fixed 1200px design width inside a CSS-transformed preview container. `vw`/`vh` reference the actual browser viewport, not the container, causing layout breaks.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
fontSize: "clamp(3rem, 12vw, 10rem)"
minHeight: "100vh"

// ✅ GOOD
fontSize: "9.5rem"          // fixed value calibrated to 1200px design width
minHeight: "780px"          // fixed px height
```

### 2. Never use `position: fixed` inside templates
`fixed` escapes the scaled preview container and overlays the editor chrome.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<nav style={{ position: "fixed", top: 0 }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<nav style={{ position: "sticky", top: 0 }}>
```

### 3. All layouts must use responsive grid/flex
Use CSS Grid or Flexbox with `flex-wrap: wrap` or responsive column counts so content reflows at smaller widths.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded two columns, breaks on mobile
display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 1fr"

// ✅ GOOD — collapses to single column below 640px
display: "grid",
gridTemplateColumns: "repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr))"
```

### 4. Font sizes must scale down on small screens
Use relative units (`rem`) sized for the 1200px design width, OR use a CSS `@media` query within the template's injected `<style>` tag.

```css
/* Inside the template's injected CSS string */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero-title { font-size: 4rem !important; }
  .works-title { font-size: 6rem !important; }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .hero-title { font-size: 2.5rem !important; }
}
```

### 5. Navigation must collapse on mobile
On screens ≤ 768px, show a hamburger menu (or stack nav links vertically). The desktop nav `display: flex` should switch to `display: none` on mobile, and vice versa for the hamburger button.

### 6. Images must be responsive
All images: `width: "100%"`, `height: "auto"`, `objectFit: "cover"`, never fixed pixel dimensions for images that are part of the layout flow.

### 7. Padding/margins must shrink on mobile
Large desktop padding (e.g. `padding: "5rem 8rem"`) must reduce on mobile to prevent content being squished.

---

## Testing Checklist (before considering a template done)
- [ ] Hero section readable on 375px wide screen
- [ ] Navigation collapses/hamburger works on mobile
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at any breakpoint
- [ ] Two-column layouts collapse to single column below 640px
- [ ] Font sizes don't overflow containers on small screens
- [ ] Images don't overflow their containers
